cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about discovering new variations of the back-propagation algorithm, which is a fundamental technique in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses an evolution-based method to discover these variations, which suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper is concerned with improving the generalization performance of the algorithm, which is a common goal in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) research. The paper also mentions using the algorithm for image classification, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the new variations in control systems, which suggests a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
